{"@context":"http://iiif.io/api/presentation/3/context.json","id":"https://digbmc.github.io/pta-manifests/phan/phan-03101/manifest.json","type":"Manifest","label":{"none":["PHAN-03101"]},"metadata":[{"label":{"none":["Timestamp"]},"value":{"none":["0:31:01"]}},{"label":{"none":["Film"]},"value":{"none":["Phantom Thread"]}},{"label":{"none":["Creator"]},"value":{"none":["Paul Thomas Anderson"]}},{"label":{"none":["Distance"]},"value":{"none":["medium shot"]}},{"label":{"none":["Angle"]},"value":{"none":["eye-level"]}},{"label":{"none":["Location"]},"value":{"none":["interior"]}},{"label":{"none":["Movement"]},"value":{"none":["mobile, tracking, pan"]}},{"label":{"none":["Composition"]},"value":{"none":["single shot"]}}],"summary":{"none":["A man picks up a box off a shelf and walks away."]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-03101/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"homepage":[{"id":"PHAN-03101","type":"Text","format":"text/html","label":{"none":["Object homepage"]}}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-03101/canvas/1","type":"Canvas","height":1080,"width":1920,"label":{"none":["PHAN-03101"]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-03101/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-03101/canvas/1/annopage-1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-03101/canvas/1/annopage-1/anno-1","type":"Annotation","motivation":"painting","target":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-03101/canvas/1","body":{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-03101/tiles/full/1920,1080/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":1080,"width":1920,"service":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-03101/tiles","type":"ImageService3","profile":"http://iiif.io/api/image/3/level0.json"}]}}]}],"annotations":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-03101/canvas/1/page/p1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-03101/canvas/1/584dca0c-0620-4424-8a69-3574a13dd618","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-06-30T13:47:22.519Z","creator":"g","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>Sina Movaghati situates <em>Phantom Thread</em> within the tradition of 1940s Hollywood Gothic romances and film noirs that includes Leslie Arliss’s <em>The Man in Grey</em> (1943), George Cukor’s <em>Gaslight </em>(1944), Jacques Tourneur’s <em>Experiment Perilous </em>(1944), Joseph L. Mankiewicz’s <em>Dragonwyck </em>(1946) and Vincente Minnelli’s <em>Undercurrent</em> (1946). In particular, he sees Reynold’s roots in the titular figure of Edgar G. Ulmer’s <em>Bluebeard</em> (1944) (Movaghati, “Bluebeard Meets Ivy,” 713–14).&nbsp;</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-03101/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:105.63106796116507,91.0679611650485,344.8543689320388,259.4174757281553"}}}]}]}]}